{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887231387,"sessionID":"ses_284dfe4edffeXF09uj2DLyG8WE","part":{"id":"prt_d7b20a976001Cht7QL4DUibMDF","messageID":"msg_d7b209832001y3jK3PDWdY3JaT","sessionID":"ses_284dfe4edffeXF09uj2DLyG8WE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d9701a520b094ad08db00a459d92f01c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成 Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-035\n5: - **Title**: client-go 类型客户端生成\n6: - **Module**: client-go\n7: - **Language**: Go\n8: - **Size**: L\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: \n13: This delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for generating a Kubernetes client-go based typed client library for AgentCube custom resources. It defines requirements for client generation, API interfaces, informers, listers, and testing to ensure proper type-safe Kubernetes API access.\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Go module initialization and structure\n18: \n19: The system SHALL initialize a Go module with proper structure for the client-go library.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Go module initialization with correct path\n22: - **GIVEN** a client-go directory is created\n23: - **WHEN** `go mod init github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` is executed\n24: - **THEN** a go.mod file SHALL be created\n25: - **AND** the module name SHALL be github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\n26: - **AND** the Go version SHALL be 1.19 or higher\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Directory structure creation\n29: - **GIVEN** a Go module is initialized\n30: - **WHEN** the directory structure is created\n31: - **THEN** the clientset/versioned directory SHALL exist\n32: - **AND** the clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1 directory SHALL exist\n33: - **AND** the clientset/versioned/scheme directory SHALL exist\n34: - **AND** the clientset/versioned/fake directory SHALL exist\n35: - **AND** the informers/externalversions directory SHALL exist\n36: - **AND** the informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1 directory SHALL exist\n37: - **AND** the listers/runtime/v1alpha1 directory SHALL exist\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: Clientset Interface and Implementation\n40: \n41: The system SHALL provide a complete Clientset interface and implementation with proper constructors.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Clientset Interface definition\n44: - **GIVEN** the clientset/versioned/clientset.go file\n45: - **WHEN** the Interface type is defined\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL have a Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface method\n47: - **AND** it SHALL have a RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface method\n48: - **AND** the interface SHALL be complete\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Clientset struct with embedded discovery client\n51: - **GIVEN** the clientset/versioned/clientset.go file\n52: - **WHEN** the Clientset struct is defined\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL embed *discovery.DiscoveryClient\n54: - **AND** it SHALL hold runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: NewForConfig constructor\n57: - **GIVEN** a valid *rest.Config\n58: - **WHEN** NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) is called\n59: - **THEN** it SHALL return (*Clientset, error)\n60: - **AND** the Clientset SHALL be properly initialized\n61: - **AND** error SHALL be nil on success\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: NewForConfigAndClient constructor\n64: - **GIVEN** a valid *rest.Config and *http.Client\n65: - **WHEN** NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) is called\n66: - **THEN** it SHALL return (*Clientset, error)\n67: - **AND** the Clientset SHALL use the provided HTTP client\n68: - **AND** error SHALL be nil on success\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: NewForConfigOrDie constructor\n71: - **GIVEN** a valid *rest.Config\n72: - **WHEN** NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) is called\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL return *Clientset\n74: - **AND** it SHALL panic on error\n75: - **AND** the Clientset SHALL be properly initialized\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: New constructor with REST client\n78: - **GIVEN** a valid rest.Interface\n79: - **WHEN** New(c rest.Interface) is called\n80: - **THEN** it SHALL return *Clientset\n81: - **AND** the Clientset SHALL use the provided REST client\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1 group accessor\n84: - **GIVEN** a Clientset instance\n85: - **WHEN** RuntimeV1alpha1() is called\n86: - **THEN** it SHALL return runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n87: - **AND** the returned interface SHALL be properly initialized\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: RuntimeV1alpha1 Typed Client\n90: \n91: The system SHALL provide a complete typed client for the runtime.v1alpha1 API group.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: RuntimeV1alpha1Interface definition\n94: - **GIVEN** the clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go file\n95: - **WHEN** the RuntimeV1alpha1Interface type is defined\n96: - **THEN** it SHALL have a RESTClient() rest.Interface method\n97: - **AND** it SHALL embed AgentRuntimesGetter\n98: - **AND** it SHALL embed CodeInterpretersGetter\n99: - **AND** the interface SHALL be complete\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 872. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成 Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-035\n- **Title**: client-go 类型客户端生成\n- **Module**: client-go\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for generating a Kubernetes client-go based typed client library for AgentCube custom resources. It defines requirements for client generation, API interfaces, informers, listers, and testing to ensure proper type-safe Kubernetes API access.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Go module initialization and structure\n\nThe system SHALL initialize a Go module with proper structure for the client-go library.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775887231377,"end":1775887231384}}}}
